</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/dobenet/pics/tsymbol.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> Everyone makes it a big deal when a church gets burned. Once a church is burned the whole nation knows about it before the ashes stop smoking, but what if the Federal Government burns a church?<br>
<br>
There is an area near where I live called &quot;Between the Rivers&quot;, or &quot;Land Between the Lakes&quot;.  This community is/was somewhat issolated and things change much slower there. Families live in the same household for generations and most people farm the same land for many generations.<br>
<br>
These people were quite happy with their lives, but The Federal Government in its infinite wisdom decided that these people needed to be modernized. The people here had developled their own sub-culture here which is/was completely unique to this area.  The Federal Government knowing that the best way to destroy a culture is to destroy the religion (lots of practice at this with Native Americans) decided to bulldoze and burn 2 of the 3 churches in this area. The third was hidden from the government and is being restored. The government found out about the restoration and tried to have it demolished as well, but the case was taken to the courts and the government lost.<br>
<br>
Now I bet that none of you ever heard of this. I know for a fact that it was never on the news here and I live 30 mins from the place. Does the government have the right to tell people how to live? Should those churches have been burned and why did no one put that incident on the news? <p><center><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~sewelldeanna/xani.jpg"></center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usapiens1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sapiens1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/02 2:36:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> Where people inside the charges?<br>
Was there religious icons in the churches?<br>
What was the reasons given for destroying the churches?<br>
How did they do it?<br>
<br>
<br>
This is like flag burning...<br>
<br>
It's against the law... but att he same time... burning is the only way to respectfully &quot;dispose&quot; of a flag once it has gotten to a certain point.<br>
<br>
I would like to hear more details.<br>
 <p>Sapiens Soultracker<br>
Robustus Magnus
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uxanivusaurelius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xanivus Aurelius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/02 4:36:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/dobenet/pics/tsymbol.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> People still used these Churches Rob. The buildings were in good order. They weren't falling down etc.... I do not know the reason the government said they did it. The real reason they did do it was to destroy the culture that these people had formed. Why did the government want to destroy their culture? Because these people were &quot;behind the times&quot;. They were happy and were breaking no laws. My question is, what right does the government have to tell us how to live and to do something so wretched as to destroy a place of worship?<br>
<br>
btw, this is far different from Flag burning. There is a huge differance between Nationality and Religion. A people's religion is the strongest definition of their culture and it can be a huge shock to see a place of worship destroyed.  <br>
<br>
Don't ask for more details. Accept that this happened against the will of the people that built and worshiped. The government had no right to destroy these buildings.  How would you like it if someone came and told you that you were living in a wrong way and attempted to make you change it? <p><center><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~sewelldeanna/xani.jpg"></center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usapiens1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sapiens1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/02 5:42:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> We do it all the time to other countries... We go in torch their cities and tell them how to do things....<br>
<br>
I think if half of what you describe is happened.. this is really really wrong... but doesn;t surprise me... under Bush things like this will become commonalities...<br>
 <p>Sapiens Soultracker<br>
Robustus Magnus
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uxanivusaurelius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xanivus Aurelius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/02 8:44:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/dobenet/pics/tsymbol.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> It all happened Rob and this isn't some other country. This is right here in the U.S. in the &quot;Bible Belt&quot;. <p><center><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~sewelldeanna/xani.jpg"></center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uknobbie69p.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KNOBBIE69P</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/18/02 6:24:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> Xanivus,<br>
<br>
Unless you are under 16 years old then you don't really expect me to believe that you think we really are the &quot;Land of the Free&quot;?<br>
<br>
Our government has been imposing sanctions on us from its inception. From your local government on up to our beloved federal government we are told everything from what we can eat and what we can wear, where we can cross the street, what time we have to turn our stereos down in the evening, and even what types of sexual relations are illegal with our spouses. Yes, oral and anal sex is illegal in some states.<br>
<br>
Now as far as the church incidents are concerned I see only one way to find out for sure what the problem is. Send a petition around to your local townsfolk and ship the fucker off to 60 minutes, 20/20, Dateline and whatever other news show there is and ask them for an answer to this. Then let the government get them an answer.<br>
<br>
Please do not try to link these 2 incidents to the YEARS of abuse and slaughter and theft that the government has imposed on the American Indian. This pales in comparison.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uxanivusaurelius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xanivus Aurelius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/18/02 12:46:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/dobenet/pics/tsymbol.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> Wow, I start a post to make it clear that our government isn't the shining city on a hill we make it out to be, and someone reads it bass ackwards and calls me a ignorant 16 year old. Every other place I posted realized my point. <p><center><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~sewelldeanna/xani.jpg"></center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uknobbie69p.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KNOBBIE69P</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/18/02 1:02:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> I am not saying that at all xan. I, in all my 33 years of wisdom, have always believed that our government has run our lives. <br>
<br>
Call me a conspiracy theorist if you will.<br>
<br>
Who is to say that with all the DNA advancements that the government doesn't already have a storage facility with the DNA blueprint of every newborn baby for the past few years?<br>
<br>
All I was saying is that I couldn't believe that you question at all whether or not the government has the right to run our lives. <br>
<br>
Blame falls on our founding fathers because with the declaration of independance(which essentially was the demise of the american indian) came the US Constitution and our &quot;Bill of Rights&quot;.<br>
<br>
I would have loved to live back in the day where there were no laws and I could ride my horse to the saloon. If I do that today I would get a RWI. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ukattriaminx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kattria Minx </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/6/02 9:06:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Church Burnings</span><hr size=1> What are the denomination of the churches? What was the reason given for demolition?<br>
<br>
Where did this take place? Can you offer any links so we can check for ourselves the veracity of this?<br>
<br>
Something tells me there's more to the story than just &quot;the government tore down churches for no reason.&quot;<br>
<br>
EDIT: a quick google search indicated that this area is publicly owned, meaning that the government owns it, and barring things like endangering species or violating EPA regs, they can do what they want with the land. Somehow I don't think baptists will be endangered as a result of razing a church.<br>
<br>
Maybe the churches should have moved to someone's private land. Then they wouldn't have been torn down. <p><center>Kattria Minx<br>
